byline.original: By MICHAEL J. DE LA MERCED and BEN PROTESS

abstract: The Commodity Futures Trading Commission and Interactive Brokers, a Connecticut-based brokerage firm, had raised questions about capital levels.
snippet: The Commodity Futures Trading Commission and Interactive Brokers, a Connecticut-based brokerage firm, had raised questions about capital levels.
lead_paragraph: MF Global confirmed in a bankruptcy filing on Monday that two regulators -- the Commodity Futures Trading Commission and the Securities and Exchange Commission -- had "expressed their grave concerns" about the firm's viability.

headline.main: Regulators Had 'Grave Concerns' About MF Global
